@startuml sequence-page-render
title Plain page render — no HTMX involved (Alpine only)

actor User
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "JAX-RS route\n(consumer app)" as Route
participant "Typed model /\ntemplate data" as Model
participant "Qute engine\n(layout + component fragments)" as Qute
participant "Alpine.js" as Alpine

User -> Browser : navigate to page
Browser -> Route : GET /page
Route -> Model : build typed component models
Route -> Qute : render full page\n(layout wraps component includes)
Qute --> Route : complete HTML document\n(x-data attributes inline)
Route --> Browser : 200 text/html
Browser -> Browser : parse DOM, load /web assets\n(PatternFly CSS, Alpine)
Browser -> Alpine : DOM ready, scan tree
Alpine -> Browser : hydrate x-data state
note right of Alpine
  From here, interactivity that
  needs no server data is pure
  Alpine local state — tabs,
  toggles, menus — with zero
  round-trips. HTMX only enters
  when the page wants
  server-driven updates.
end note
@enduml
